  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(18) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "And they left the house of the Lord.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "They,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " viz., the apostate princes and their following, ceased to attend the legal worship of the Temple.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And served groves and idols.—Rather, the Ashērim and the idols. (See Note on 2Chronicles 14:3.)",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "And served groves and idols.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Rather, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "the Ashērim",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " and ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "the idols.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " (See Note on ",
            "children": []
